## **1.5 PDF Text Parser (P7)**

**Module:** pdf_parser/pdf_parsers.py | **Library:** pdfplumber | **Priority Rank:** 7

| **Task** | **Description** | **Implementation Notes** | **Status** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| PDF-P7-01 | PDFTextParser — text extraction fallback | pdfplumber.extract_text() per page. Regex patterns applied to extracted text. Never overrides P1–P6 structured sources; fallback role only. parse() called only if all higher-priority adapters failed or returned UNRESOLVED. | **IMPLEMENTED** |
| PDF-P7-02 | Section lookup via regex → F-063 | RE_SECTION_NAME regex matches ISO 6162 prefixes (UB, UC, RHS, etc.). Confidence: 65 (PDF text extraction; some noise expected). IS808_LOOKUP_REQUIRED flag set due to uncertainty. | **IMPLEMENTED** |
| PDF-P7-03 | Grid/bay extraction via text annotations | Regex patterns for bay spacing text (e.g. "3 @ 5.0m = 15.0m"). Grid labels parsed. Confidence: 60 (text ambiguity). | **IMPLEMENTED** |
| PDF-P7-04 | Load data from text tables | pdfplumber.extract_tables() attempts table detection. Fallback: regex on text (e.g. "DL: 10 kN/m, LL: 5 kN/m"). Confidence: 55 (low; text parsing ambiguous). | **IMPLEMENTED** |
| PDF-P7-05 | CRITICAL: Never overrides P1–P6 | Conflict resolver rule: if field_id already has P1–P6 entry, P7 is DROPPED (ignored). P7 only populates truly absent fields. Test: T-PARSE-09 validates non-override. | **IMPLEMENTED** |
| PDF-P7-06 | Confidence hard cap ≤ 85 | PDF_TEXT confidence capped at 85 in FieldExtraction.__post_init__(). P7 base confidence 55–65; cap applied automatically. | **IMPLEMENTED** |
| PDF-P7-07 | Historical prohibition (P8 applies; P7 does not) | P7 is structured text, not OCR. Historical prohibition applies only to P8 (PDF Image). P7 can populate any field unless conflict rules prohibit. | **IMPLEMENTED** |
| PDF-P7-08 | Source priority & fallback chain | source_type = PDF_TEXT, priority_rank = 7. Fallback-only source; never called unless P1–P6 unavailable or all UNRESOLVED for field_id. | **IMPLEMENTED** |

**PDF Text Source Priority:** PRIORITY_RANK = 7 (P7 fallback; never overrides P1–P6)

**Key Risk (RISK-B5-05):** Regex-based text parsing vulnerable to PDF encoding errors and layout variations. Mitigation: confidence capped at 65 (lower than structured sources). Conflict resolver prevents override of higher-priority sources.

