## **1.6 PDF Image / OCR Parser (P8)**

**Module:** pdf_parser/pdf_parsers.py | **Library:** PyMuPDF + Tesseract | **Priority Rank:** 8

| **Task** | **Description** | **Implementation Notes** | **Status** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| PDF-P8-01 | PDFImageParser — OCR-based extraction | fitz.open() reads PDF. Pages with text_dict() check; if text sparse, page rasterized to image. Tesseract-ocr applied. confidence_score automatically capped at 75 in FieldExtraction.__post_init__() regardless of OCR confidence. | **IMPLEMENTED** |
| PDF-P8-02 | Page rasterization for OCR | pdf_page.get_pixmap() → PNG. Tesseract processes PNG. OCR confidence extracted from Tesseract output. Hard cap 75 enforced — no exceptions. | **IMPLEMENTED** |
| PDF-P8-03 | CRITICAL: Historical prohibition for governing fields | FieldExtraction.__post_init__() checks: if field_id is governing field (F-001, F-005, F-010, etc.) AND source_type == PDF_IMAGE, auto-set status = UNRESOLVED with flag HISTORICAL_PROHIBITED. Override P8 confidence to 0. | **IMPLEMENTED** |
| PDF-P8-04 | OCR-mandatory-review flag | If Tesseract confidence < 80 OR page contains mixed fonts/rotated text, set flag: OCR_USED_MANDATORY_REVIEW. Status: PENDING_REVIEW (not POPULATED). | **IMPLEMENTED** |
| PDF-P8-05 | Confidence hard cap ≤ 75 | PDF_IMAGE confidence hard-capped at 75 in FieldExtraction.__post_init__() before any conflict resolution. Adapters cannot inflate; cap enforced at dataclass level. | **IMPLEMENTED** |
| PDF-P8-06 | Fallback-only, lowest priority | source_type = PDF_IMAGE, priority_rank = 8. P8 only called if P1–P7 all fail or return UNRESOLVED. Conflict resolver yields P8 to all higher sources. | **IMPLEMENTED** |
| PDF-P8-07 | OCR language & character set | Tesseract config: eng (English) + osd (Orientation and Script Detection). config: --psm 6 (assume single block of text). Handles rotated pages. | **IMPLEMENTED** |
| PDF-P8-08 | Source priority & OCR integration | source_type = PDF_IMAGE, priority_rank = 8. All FieldExtraction objects carry: extraction_method = OCR, confidence ≤ 75, status possibly UNRESOLVED + HISTORICAL_PROHIBITED, flags possibly OCR_USED_MANDATORY_REVIEW. | **IMPLEMENTED** |

**PDF Image / OCR Source Priority:** PRIORITY_RANK = 8 (P8 lowest; never overrides P1–P7; govering fields auto-UNRESOLVED)

**Key Risk (RISK-B5-06):** Tesseract OCR vulnerable to poor scans, non-English text, non-standard fonts. Mitigation: confidence hard cap 75 + Historical prohibition guard + OCR_USED_MANDATORY_REVIEW flag ensures all P8 data flagged for manual review.

