## **1.7 Archive Extractor (Utility)**

**Module:** archive_extractor/archive_extractor.py | **Library:** zipfile + rarfile | **Priority Rank:** N/A (utility; not source adapter)

| **Task** | **Description** | **Implementation Notes** | **Status** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| AR-01 | ArchiveExtractor — ZIP / RAR handler | Detects file extension (.zip, .rar). Validates archive format via magic bytes. _extract_zip() and _extract_rar() implemented. | **IMPLEMENTED** |
| AR-02 | Encrypted archive detection | If archive password-protected, raises RuntimeError with flag: ESCALATE_IT + message. No extraction attempted; user/IT must provide password or unencrypted copy. | **IMPLEMENTED** |
| AR-03 | Member file enumeration | _list_members() returns tuple (member_paths, member_metadata). Metadata includes original size, compression, CRC. | **IMPLEMENTED** |
| AR-04 | Safe extraction to temp directory | Extract to temp isolated directory (/tmp/ifs_extract_<uuid>). Files not extracted to project root. temp_dir cleaned up post-processing. Path traversal protection: member path validation before extraction. | **IMPLEMENTED** |
| AR-05 | Nested archive support | If archive contains nested archive (.zip inside .zip), log INFO + add to member list. Extraction is non-recursive (only top level extracted). | **IMPLEMENTED** |
| AR-06 | File type classification post-extraction | Extracted files scanned for .dxf, .dwg, .xlsx, .pdf, .xml, .txt extensions. Project parse pipeline invokes appropriate adapter per file type. No FieldExtraction output from extractor itself (utility role). | **IMPLEMENTED** |

**Archive Extractor Role:** Utility; not a field-value source adapter. Prepares multi-file projects for sequential parsing.

**Key Risk (RISK-B5-07):** Encrypted archives block extraction. Mitigation: ESCALATE_IT flag with clear user message.

