# **2. SQLite Output Status**

**Status: ALL ADAPTERS PRODUCE NORMALIZED FieldExtraction OUTPUT**

All 7 adapters (ETABS P3, Prota DXF P4, Prota PDF P5, DWG/DXF P6, PDF Text P7, PDF Image P8, Archive utility) inherit BaseParser and produce FieldExtraction objects compliant with §4.2 contract (Block 1 baseline).

## **2.1 Normalized Output Contract Enforcement**

Each FieldExtraction object carries:

| **Attribute** | **Enforced Value** | **Adapter Responsibility** | **Dataclass Guard** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| field_id | F-001 to F-196; validated against field_master | Adapter populates correct F-field | ValueError if invalid |
| value | Normalized string | Adapter calls normalise_*() methods | Required; no None |
| raw_value | Original pre-normalization | Adapter stores raw source text | Required; audit trail |
| confidence_score | Hard caps enforced: PDF_TEXT ≤ 85, PDF_IMAGE ≤ 75, others ≤ 95 | Adapter assigns base; __post_init__() applies cap | __post_init__() reduces if cap exceeded |
| source_type | SourceType enum (ETABS, PROTA_DXF, PROTA_PDF, DWG_DXF_GENERIC, PDF_TEXT, PDF_IMAGE) | Adapter class constant | Enum validation |
| priority_rank | 3–8 per source_priority_master | Adapter class constant (PRIORITY_RANK) | Value range check |
| extraction_method | Enum: structured_keyword, table_lookup, text_regex, OCR, derived | Adapter selects based on parsing method | Enum validation |
| status | FieldStatus enum (POPULATED, UNRESOLVED, DERIVED_BROKEN, PENDING_REVIEW) | Adapter sets; UNRESOLVED for absent/corrupt fields | Enum validation |
| member_ref | Optional; member-scoped extractions (section name per member) | Adapter populates if applicable | String or None |
| page_ref | Optional; page/section reference in source file | Adapter logs if available (PDF page, Excel sheet, DXF layer) | String or None |
| flags | List[str]; FB-RULE-xxx, ESCALATE_IT, OCR_USED_MANDATORY_REVIEW, etc. | Adapter appends per business rules | List validation |
| extracted_at | ISO-8601 UTC timestamp | Auto-populated by dataclass __post_init__() | datetime.now(UTC) |

## **2.2 Hard Confidence Caps (Enforced at __post_init__)**

```python
# Pseudocode: FieldExtraction.__post_init__()
if self.source_type == PDF_TEXT and self.confidence_score > 85:
    self.confidence_score = 85
elif self.source_type == PDF_IMAGE and self.confidence_score > 75:
    self.confidence_score = 75
elif self.source_type == PDF_IMAGE and self._is_governing_field(self.field_id):
    self.status = UNRESOLVED
    self.confidence_score = 0
    self.flags.append("HISTORICAL_PROHIBITED")
```

## **2.3 ParserOutput Container**

Each parse() method returns ParserOutput object:

```python
ParserOutput(
    source_file_path: str,
    source_type: SourceType,
    parser_name: str,
    extractions: List[FieldExtraction],
    parse_success: bool,
    parse_duration_ms: float,
    warnings: List[str],
    errors: List[str],
    flags: List[str]
)
```

All 7 adapters populate ParserOutput with lists of FieldExtraction objects. No exceptions escape parse(); all errors captured in errors[] and flags[].

