# **3. Confidence / Source Metadata Status**

**Status: ALL ADAPTERS CORRECTLY TAG SOURCE AND CONFIDENCE**

## **3.1 Source Priority Hierarchy**

Confirmed order per conflict_resolver (Block 6 onwards):

| **Rank** | **Source** | **Priority** | **Confidence Range** | **Override Behavior** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | STAAD | P1 | 90–95 | Wins all conflicts |
| 2 | MBS | P2 | 75–90 | Yields to P1 |
| 3 | ETABS | P3 | 70–85 | Yields to P1–P2 |
| 4 | Prota DXF | P4 | 60–75 | Yields to P1–P3 |
| 5 | Prota PDF | P5 | 70–75 | Yields to P1–P4 |
| 6 | DWG/DXF | P6 | 50–75 | Yields to P1–P5 |
| 7 | PDF Text | P7 | 55–65 | Yields to P1–P6; never override |
| 8 | PDF Image/OCR | P8 | 0–75 | Yields to all; governing fields UNRESOLVED |

## **3.2 Extraction Method Tags**

Each FieldExtraction.extraction_method explicitly identifies parsing strategy:

| **Method** | **Confidence** | **Sources Using** | **Example** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **structured_keyword** | 90–95 | STAAD (block keywords), MBS (XML keys), ETABS (column lookup), Prota (layer/block names) | "MEMBER PROPERTY TA ST UB 300×300×10" → F-063 = "UB 300×300×10", confidence 95 |
| **table_lookup** | 85–90 | STAAD (bolt table columns), MBS (XML table), ETABS (load table), Prota (dimension blocks) | Bolt table: GRADE column → F-083, confidence 90 |
| **text_regex** | 55–75 | PDF Text (regex on extracted text), MBS (fallback text regex), all (field confirmation) | "3 @ 5.0m" → grid spacing 5.0m, confidence 65 |
| **OCR** | 0–75 (capped) | PDF Image/OCR | Scanned PDF section label → F-063, confidence ≤ 75 |
| **derived** | 50–70 | Prota DXF (geometry inference), DWG/DXF (spatial proximity) | Topology inferred from member endpoints → member_start/member_end, confidence 65, status DERIVED |

## **3.3 Confidence Score Assignment Rules**

**ETABS (P3):**
- Openpyxl cell extraction: 80
- Table cell certainty: 85
- Hard cap: 85
- Load fallback (if MBS missing): 85

**Prota DXF (P4):**
- Geometric coordinate: 65
- Section hint from label: 65
- Hard cap: 75

**Prota PDF (P5):**
- Structured table (pdfplumber): 75
- Regex on text: 70
- Hard cap: 85

**DWG/DXF Generic (P6):**
- Native DXF: 65
- DWG converted: 60 (−5 for conversion uncertainty)
- ODA R14 risk: 50
- Hard cap: 75

**PDF Text (P7):**
- Regex on extracted text: 60–65
- Table detection: 70
- Hard cap: 85

**PDF Image / OCR (P8):**
- Tesseract OCR output: up to 90 (base)
- Hard cap: 75 (enforced)
- Governing field: 0 + HISTORICAL_PROHIBITED
- PENDING_REVIEW if Tesseract < 80: 0 (not populated until reviewed)

## **3.4 Source Type Constants (Class-Level)**

Each adapter defines source_type and priority_rank as class constants:

```python
class ETABSParser(BaseParser):
    ADAPTER_NAME = "ETABS Excel Adapter"
    SOURCE_TYPE = SourceType.ETABS
    PRIORITY_RANK = 3

class ProtaParser(BaseParser):  # Dual-mode (DXF + PDF)
    ADAPTER_NAME = "Prota CAD Adapter"
    SOURCE_TYPE = SourceType.PROTA_DXF  # or PROTA_PDF depending on file
    PRIORITY_RANK = 4  # or 5

class CADParser(BaseParser):
    ADAPTER_NAME = "DWG/DXF Generic Adapter"
    SOURCE_TYPE = SourceType.DWG_DXF_GENERIC
    PRIORITY_RANK = 6

class PDFTextParser(BaseParser):
    ADAPTER_NAME = "PDF Text Parser"
    SOURCE_TYPE = SourceType.PDF_TEXT
    PRIORITY_RANK = 7

class PDFImageParser(BaseParser):
    ADAPTER_NAME = "PDF Image / OCR Parser"
    SOURCE_TYPE = SourceType.PDF_IMAGE
    PRIORITY_RANK = 8
```

All FieldExtraction objects produced by these adapters carry matching source_type and priority_rank.

